summary:
I'm a mechanical engineer with a Professional Masterâ€™s Degree from the University Department of Professional Studies in Split. 
As a student, I had experience working in the service department for Suzuki where I gained knowledge of mechanics in practice. I also had to get my hands dirty.
During my last year at college, I started to work in an R&D department in a start-up company Enamel. There I got skills in 3D printing, prototyping and design. Due to the nature of working in a start-up company, I also gained a lot of soft skills. 
Afterwards, I started working in a technical department in the company Deltron which is my first experience working in a big company. There I gots skills in HVAC design and equipment but also helping customers and users with our equipment.
I am a problem-solving, curious and communicative individual with a strong work ethic ready to get out of my comfort zone for new challenges.
